  -- For the i-th term: (y i - x i) * (deriv f ((1 - t) • x + t • y) i)
  -- The derivative is:
  -- (y i - x i) * (deriv (fun s ↦ (deriv f ((1 - s) • x + s • y) i)) t)
  -- Let's compute the derivative inside:
  -- deriv (fun s ↦ (deriv f ((1 - s) • x + s • y) i)) t
  -- Use the chain rule: deriv (h(s)) = deriv (deriv f (g(s))) i * deriv g(s)
  -- where g(s) = (1 - s) • x + s • y
  -- deriv g(s) = y - x, so the i-th component is y i - x i
  -- So deriv (fun s ↦ (deriv f (g(s)) i)) t = (deriv (deriv f) (g(t)) i) * (y i - x i)
