`∂H/∂x_j` is `if j = i then (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y) else 0`.
So, `deriv/dt [ H(t) ] = (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y) * (-x_i + y_i)`.
Therefore, `d/dt [ (y i - x i) * (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y) ] = (y i - x i) * (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y) * (-x_i + y_i)`.
This is `(y i - x i)^2 * (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`.

This still does not match. Let's think about the structure of `interpolated_deriv2`.
`∑ i, ∑ j, (y i - x i) * (y j - x j) * (nth_partial i <| nth_partial j f) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`
This is `∑ i, ∑ j, (y i - x i) * (y j - x j) * (∂^2 f / ∂x_i ∂x_j) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`.

To get this from the derivative of `interpolated_deriv`, we need to apply the differentiation rules correctly.
The function is `F(t) = ∑ i, (y i - x i) * (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y)`.
`F'(t) = ∑ i, deriv/dt [ (y i - x i) * (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y) ]`.
As calculated, this is `∑ i, (y i - x i) * (∂f/∂x_i) ((1 - t) • x + t • y) * (-x_i + y_i)`.
